  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Lifesaving Shelter/NFI Provision to conflict-affected IDPs in Afar, Amhara and Tigray</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this IOM project is to provide life-saving emergency shelter and non-food items to internally displaced persons in conflict-affected areas of Amhara, Afar and Tigray.
With this CERF grant, IOM will mainly provide NFI Kits to 11,000 households, Emergency shelter kits to 9,000 households, rental cash transfer to 3,500 households, and will rehabilitate 15 communal shelters and collective sites.    
The project covers Emergency shelters/Non-food Items sector and will last six months. It will benefit 151,250 persons (including 22,688 girls, 60,500 women and 23,660 persons with disabilities).</narrative>
  </description>
